records.addlTxt:
Defendant Demarco Lee As-Saffat in court with attorney Thomas E Harris.  Defendant Demarco Lee As-Saffat in custody.  Joshua M Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
At the hour of 10:28 a.m. the jury returned and by the Foreperson brought in verdicts that were then and there read by the Court.  
-We, the jury, find the Defendant Guilty of Child Enticement, in manner and form as charged in Count #1 of the Information;
-We, the jury, find the Defendant Guilty of Second Degree Sexual Assault of a Child, in manner and form as charged in Count #2 of the Information;
-We, the jury, find the Defendant Guilty of Obstructing an Officer, in manner and form as charged in Count #3 of the Information;
-We, the jury, find the Defendant Guilty of Obstructing an Officer, in manner and form as charged in Count #4 of the Information.
Court polled the jury and each juror acknowledged the correctness of the verdicts.  Verdicts received and filed. Court discharged the jury.  State motion for judgment on the verdict granted by the Court subject to motions after verdict. Exhibit list, in writing, received and filed.  Case adjourned to 9-15-2014 at 8:30 a.m. 
for Sentencing Hearing in Branch 10.
